  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Reference [56] proposed a pedestrian detection method based on an improved FPN.",
    "They utilized the lower layers of a feature pyramid network to predict and detect objects at different scales.",
    "Recognizing the challenge of obtaining useful information to accurately detect small-scale and occluded objects, their method utilizes densely connected blocks to enrich semantic information.",
    "A dense connectivity block is a combination of a channel attention module and a global attention module.",
    "The channel attention module assigns weights to each channel based on its importance, directing the network to emphasize the visible part of the pedestrian and address target occlusion.These approaches leverage context information to enhance the performance of object detection algorithms in traffic scenarios, where challenges such as occlusion, varying viewpoints, and complex backgrounds are prevalent."
  ],
